and they want it to go faster
but all the app is at the end of the day is just a webview
is this for private use?
yeah
i open a port forward and then all the web code from the server takes over

unless there is some kind of magical port forwarding speed up function i missed
depends, have you determined the bottleneck?
if possible you may see better performance on a VPN which will likely have a more efficient encryption algo
yeah, I’m using JSch which is just a pure java implementation of libssh2
but all the security algo stuff is just java.security
sure, encryption was just a guess to the bottleneck. You would need to check what the real bottleneck is if any on the device

At the end of the day I'm just loading a web page into an android webview
It just happens to be over a forwarded port
could be entirely unforeseen specially with java based libs that can sometimes depend on class loaders eating memory and/or CPU in unexpected ways under the dalvik vm
